      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the great court.—‘Azārāh, “court,” a late word, common in the Targums for the classical hāqēr, which has just occurred. The ‘azārāh was the outer court of the temple. It is not mentioned at all in the parallel narrative. The LXX. calls it “the great court;” the Vulg., “the great basilica.” The Syriac renders the whole verse: “And he made one great court for the priests and Levites, and covered the doors and bolts with bronze.” (Comp. Note on 2Chronicles 4:3 for this plating of the doors with bronze.) The bronze plated doors of Shalmaneser’s palace at Balawat were twenty-two feet high, and each leaf was six feet wide.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And the great court.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—‘",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Azārāh, “",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "court,” a late word, common in the Targums for the classical ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "hāqēr,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " which has just occurred. The ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "‘azārāh",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " was the outer court of the temple. It is not mentioned at all in the parallel narrative. The LXX. calls it “the great court;” the Vulg., “the great basilica.” The Syriac renders the whole verse: “And he made one great court for the priests and Levites, and covered the doors and bolts with bronze.” (Comp. Note on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 4:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " for this plating of the doors with bronze.) The bronze plated doors of Shalmaneser’s palace at ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Balawat",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " were twenty-two feet high, and each leaf was six feet wide.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
