  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "9, 10. The Two Courts",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the court of the priests, and the great court",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] There is a difficulty in this mention of two Temple courts by the Chronicler, for it may be doubted whether Solomon’s Temple, strictly speaking, had more than ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "one",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " court, for in “the other court” stood Solomon’s house (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 7:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). This “other court” seems to be called the “middle court” (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 20:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and the “higher court” (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 36:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The “great court” (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 7:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") was perhaps a third court containing not only the king’s house, but all the royal buildings as well. The Heb. word for “court” in all the above passages is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "ḥâçer",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but here the “court (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "ḥâççr",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") of the priests” is distinguished from a court called the “great court” (Heb. “great ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Azârâh",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "”). Perhaps the Chronicler wishes to make the same distinction when he says that Solomon’s great prayer was offered (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 6:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") in “the court” (Heb. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Azârâh",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
